                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Turner</ln>
                        <fn>Claude Eugene</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Turner</ln>
                        <fn>A. J.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Prof.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Turner</ln>
                        <fn>Kate M.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Claude Eugene Turner, son of Prof. A. J. and Kate M. Turner, died of
                    typhoid fever on May 11th. He was 9 years old.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="o">
                <column>02</column>
                <head>Deaths</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>McComb</ln>
                        <fn>James</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>James McComb died of dropsy of the chest at Barterbrook on May 9th. He was
                    "upwards of 70 years of age."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="o">
                <column>02</column>
                <head>Deaths</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Ide</ln>
                        <fn>Ella Franklin</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Ide</ln>
                        <fn>Annie Baldwin</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Ide</ln>
                        <fn>Louis</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Ella Franklin Ide and Annie Baldwin Ide, daughters of Louis Ide, died on
                    May 4th. The girls were 8 and 6 respectively. "Weep not for those whom the veil
                    of the tomb/In life's happy morning, hath hid from our eyes/Ere sin threw a
                    blight o'er the spirit's young bloom,/Or earth hath profaned what was born for
                    the skies,/Death chill'd the fair fountain, ere sorrow had stained it./'Twas
                    forzen in all the pure light of its course,/And but sleeps till the sunshine of
                    Heaven has unchain'd it,/To water that Eden where first was its source.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote/>
        </page>
